parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump flange can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to accidents, fires, or explosions, and put the rider's safety at risk.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel pump
cracks in the fuel pump flange
broken fuel pump flange
fuel spraying or pouring out while the motorcycle is in motion
fuel covering the rider
fuel pooling on the exhaust or surrounding areas.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Tank Flange Cracking and Leaking
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking of the fuel tank flanges can cause gasoline to leak onto the engine and hot exhaust, creating a fire hazard and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Gasoline leaks from the fuel tank
puddles in the fuel pump area
and drips down the motorcycle tank onto the engine and hot exhaust.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the rider to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge fails to accurately display the fuel level
causing the rider to run out of fuel
and in some cases
the mileage and miles left displays do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the engine to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the rider stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The engine stops while driving
the motorcycle will not restart for several minutes
and error codes indicate fuel pump failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS pump can cause the loss of Anti-lock Braking System (ABS) functionality, leading to reduced vehicle safety and increased risk of accidents. Additionally, it can also cause the speedometer to malfunction and the brake warning light to illuminate.
symptoms: The "Brake Failure" warning light illuminates
the speedometer is inoperative
the ABS system is not functioning
the brake warning light is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive can cause vibration, smoke, and odor, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents. Repeated failures can result in significant repair costs and downtime.
symptoms: Vibration felt while driving
vibration worsens under power and diminishes when power is reduced
smoke and odor from the front drive shaft U-joint area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front drive shaft U-joint can cause vibration, smoke, and odor, leading to a loss of vehicle control and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Vibration felt while driving
vibration worsens under power and diminishes when power is reduced
smoke and odor from the front drive shaft U-joint area.
